New Records: Zack Wheeler and Zac Gallen are the starting pitchers for the Phillies and D-backs, respectively, in Game 5 of the NLCS. Wheeler has a 2.37 ERA with 26 strikeouts and 1 walk in three postseason games, while Gallen has been the team's ace with a 3.47 ERA in the regular season.
Key Match Events: The Phillies and D-backs used a combined 16 pitchers in Game 4, suggesting a bullpen game approach, and Game 5 will likely rely on their aces, Wheeler and Gallen, to determine the winner.
Pre-Game Insights: Phillies manager Rob Thomson emphasized the importance of having their ace, Zack Wheeler, on the mound for Game 5. D-backs manager Torey Lovullo mentioned relying on Zac Gallen's length and performance in the regular season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game will be played at 8 p.m. ET on October 21st at Chase Field, airing on TBS. The starting lineups include notable players like Bryce Harper, Trea Turner, and Corbin Carroll.
